spans.text: hallowed name to harps of Seraphs sung
a sudden peace , Till every worldly thought within me dies , And earth's gay pageants
a sudden peace , Till every worldly thought within me dies , And earth's gay pageants
My soul submits to wear her wonted yoke
My soul submits to wear her wonted yoke
the first wish to better hopes inclined
the language of a silent tear
the soft hand of winning pleasure
with strong confidence lay hold on thee
kiss the sceptre , or the rod , While GOD is seen in all , and all in GOD
While GOD is seen in all , and all in GOD
the voice of GOD among the trees
